<h2><strong>How to use</strong></h2>
<ul>
 	<li><strong>Substitute</strong>Â for tomato or tamarind to make a zestier dal or curry.</li>
 	<li>Make<strong>Â rasam</strong> by soaking and boiling the peel in water. Use 1 cup of water for every 2 kokum peels. Add salt and sugar to the mixture once boiled. On the side, briefly heat mustard seeds, chili and cumin in oil. Add these spices to the kokum water concoction. Serve the rasam with rice or serve as a soup.</li>
 	<li>Make <strong>kokum kadi,</strong> a famous sour, savory beverage made by combining dried coconut, salt and green chilies with kokum syrup and water.</li>
